Steps:

BUILD:
1. pip install virtualenv
2. To use venv in your project, in your terminal, create a new project folder, cd to the project folder in your terminal, and run the following command:
    - mkdir projectA
    - cd projectA
    - python3 -m venv env : python<version> -m venv <virtual-environment-name>
3.0 check if windows or linux
3. Linux: source env/bin/activate
   Windows: env/Scripts/activate.bat
            env/Scripts/Activate.ps1
4. Install libraries/packages:
    https://spacy.io/usage/models
    - pip install package_name

5. Freeze Dependencies. Include .env to .gitignore
6. Recreate environment to others:
   python -m venv myenv
   source myenv/bin/activate  # Activate the environment
   pip install -r requirements.txt

7. Create a bin directory
8. Go to the bin directory
9. Clone the whisper api
    - git clone https://github.com/ggerganov/whisper.cpp.git
10. Go to the whisper.cpp directory
11. Download the 3 models: bash ./models/download-ggml-model.sh small/medium/large
12. Put the 3 models to the root of bin folder
13. Build the program using make
14. Put the main program to root of bin 


MAIN:

1 Get the audio file to parse
1.1 or if youtube -> yt-dlp -x --audio-format wav --audio-quality 16K --postprocessor-args "-ar 16000" https://www.youtube.com/watch\?v\=yWDsP7CWfQ8
2. Resample to 16K audio to 16K if not yet then change the name to output.wav if not yet
3. Check the threads_num then use it as parameter
3. Run the program ./main -m <model.bin> -t <threads_num> -otxt -l Japanese -f <path/to/audio>
4. Parse the 

